content.prompt:
You are an SEO content strategist. Given the seed topic "<SEED>" build a pillar-cluster topic map.
Output a JSON object: { "pillar": { "title": "...", "primary_keyword": "...", "search_intent": "informational", "target_word_count": 3000 }, "clusters": [ { "title": "...", "primary_keyword": "...", "search_intent": "informational|commercial|transactional", "target_word_count": 1200, "people_also_ask": ["...", "...", "..."], "internal_links_to": ["pillar", "cluster-slug-1", "cluster-slug-2"] } ] }
Requirements: - 8-30 clusters that collectively cover the topic exhaustively. - No two clusters target overlapping keywords (avoid cannibalisation). - Mix intents: ~60% informational, ~30% commercial, ~10% transactional. - Each cluster includes 3+ "People Also Ask" questions sourced from real SERPs. - Every cluster links back to pillar plus 2-4 sibling clusters.
